WEBVTT

00:04.670 --> 00:07.420
♪ Magic is real here ♪

00:07.500 --> 00:10.000
♪ Far away from home ♪

00:10.090 --> 00:12.420
♪ Anything can happen ♪

00:12.510 --> 00:15.390
♪ When witches make the rules ♪

00:15.470 --> 00:17.760
♪ Monsters are cool ♪

00:17.850 --> 00:20.770
♪ The moon is our friend ♪

00:20.850 --> 00:23.100
♪ I wanna stay with you ♪

00:23.180 --> 00:26.560
♪ On Summer Camp Island ♪

00:28.820 --> 00:32.740
♪♪

00:32.820 --> 00:34.030
[ Slurps ]

00:34.110 --> 00:35.530
Mortimer: It's no use.

00:35.610 --> 00:40.580
I'm destined to be alone
in a club of one forever!

00:40.660 --> 00:42.250
[ Sobbing ]

00:42.330 --> 00:43.580
Whoop.

00:43.660 --> 00:45.330
I know you're sad because
you didn't get into

00:45.420 --> 00:47.790
the Moss and Scones
Secret Society

00:47.880 --> 00:51.130
but what if we make
our own secret society?

00:51.210 --> 00:53.170
An official
secret society?

00:53.260 --> 00:56.130
You don't belong until
you officially belong.

00:56.220 --> 00:58.430
Yes.
It'll be official.

00:58.510 --> 01:03.430
We'll have members and rituals
and feelings.

01:03.520 --> 01:06.100
Hedgehog and I do this kind
of stuff all the time.

01:06.190 --> 01:09.480
Make your own secret society.
Yes!

01:09.560 --> 01:12.280
We can meet here
in this abandoned classroom.

01:12.360 --> 01:15.150
Ooh!
I could even be president!

01:17.530 --> 01:20.870
Every group needs a leader
to get its feet off the ground.

01:20.950 --> 01:22.910
Like George Washington himself,

01:22.990 --> 01:26.080
I will escort our fledgling
nation of feelings

01:26.160 --> 01:29.040
to sturdier days.

01:29.130 --> 01:31.670
Um, what did you
and your Hedgehog

01:31.750 --> 01:34.630
do after you drafted
your secret society charter?

01:34.710 --> 01:35.920
Ask our friends
to join!

01:36.010 --> 01:38.340
I don't have any friends,
remember?

01:38.430 --> 01:43.010
Wait, so you don't know Ava
or Howard or anyone else?

01:43.100 --> 01:45.390
-Who?
-Oh, right.

01:45.480 --> 01:48.100
You can't have friends
without feelings.

01:48.190 --> 01:50.440
Feelings make friends
and friends make feelings,

01:50.520 --> 01:55.190
and they feed off each other
in an endless feedback loop.

01:55.280 --> 01:56.950
One sec.

01:58.700 --> 01:59.780
Oh.

01:59.860 --> 02:02.200
Do you think
anyone's gonna come?

02:02.280 --> 02:04.450
Oh, yeah, I sent them
personal invitations

02:04.540 --> 02:06.700
to get them interested.

02:06.790 --> 02:09.040
Here they come now!

02:09.120 --> 02:12.460
Hi, I got an invitation
saying to meet here?

02:12.540 --> 02:13.880
This is for a group of people

02:13.960 --> 02:16.800
who fall asleep
on old romance novels right?

02:16.880 --> 02:19.880
Mine says this is
for people who play violin.

02:19.970 --> 02:21.340
You play violin?

02:21.430 --> 02:23.970
Not anything that would move
someone to tears

02:24.060 --> 02:25.390
or anything like that.

02:25.470 --> 02:28.690
It's just regular emotionless
violin playing.

02:28.770 --> 02:30.940
Are we allowed to be
congregating on the lawn

02:31.020 --> 02:33.060
without a faculty advisor?

02:33.150 --> 02:37.820
One time I got a demerit for
being sad at a lost cat poster.

02:37.900 --> 02:39.900
Everything's aboveboard.

02:39.990 --> 02:41.240
Soon to be official.

02:41.320 --> 02:44.240
We have a dignitary here
from the future auditing.

02:44.330 --> 02:46.870
In fact, you've all been
brought here by him.

02:46.950 --> 02:49.410
He believes you have
an interest in...

02:49.500 --> 02:52.330
[Whispering]
...expressing yourselves.

02:52.420 --> 02:54.210
Uh...

02:54.290 --> 02:55.840
Is this a trap?

02:55.920 --> 02:57.550
I'm a real sucker
for traps.

02:57.630 --> 03:01.090
So please spare me
if you have any decency!

03:01.180 --> 03:02.970
Look, you're all
free to leave

03:03.050 --> 03:06.010
if you're not curious
about feeling freely.

03:07.520 --> 03:09.350
Hmm...

03:09.430 --> 03:11.310
To our club headquarters!

03:11.390 --> 03:16.770
♪♪

03:16.860 --> 03:18.280
[ Gasps ]

03:18.360 --> 03:19.820
Stuart!

03:19.900 --> 03:21.400
Hello, classmates.

03:21.490 --> 03:24.740
Stuart here.
Official secret society proctor.

03:24.820 --> 03:27.620
I understand you're a new
secret society?

03:28.750 --> 03:32.580
And what's the name
of your secret society?

03:32.670 --> 03:35.840
We have not decided
on a name yet.

03:35.920 --> 03:38.460
O...kay.
[ Scoffs ]

03:38.550 --> 03:41.550
And what is your secret
society motto?

03:41.630 --> 03:43.300
Still pending.

03:43.380 --> 03:44.640
Crest?

03:44.720 --> 03:46.680
Um...

03:46.760 --> 03:48.560
Listen!

03:48.640 --> 03:51.810
I take being secret society
proctor very seriously!

03:51.890 --> 03:53.940
I'll be back in morning,
and if you don't have

03:54.020 --> 03:57.570
the basic requirements
for a secret society,

03:57.650 --> 03:59.650
no club for you!

04:00.900 --> 04:03.660
Does anyone know how
a secret society decides stuff?

04:03.740 --> 04:07.280
I wonder how Moss and Scones
decided on their name.

04:07.370 --> 04:09.160
My cousin's brother's roommate
was in it!

04:09.240 --> 04:11.790
Apparently, he never told anyone
what went on in there.

04:11.870 --> 04:13.370
Not even his pet rock!

04:13.460 --> 04:15.040
Weird stuff.

04:15.120 --> 04:17.590
Creepy stuff!

04:17.670 --> 04:21.210
I know!
Let's go spy on Moss and Scones!

04:21.300 --> 04:22.920
[ All tittering ]

04:23.010 --> 04:24.470
Yeah!
There they are!

04:24.550 --> 04:26.800
Let's use those
excited emotions!

04:26.890 --> 04:28.550
Oh, shoot!

04:28.640 --> 04:30.520
Yeah, we better tamp it down.

04:30.600 --> 04:33.020
No! No! Keep those feelings
coming folks!

04:33.100 --> 04:34.350
They're welcome here!

04:34.440 --> 04:37.020
If spying brings them
out of you, huzzah!

04:37.110 --> 04:39.190
[ All cheering ]

04:39.270 --> 04:44.150
♪♪

04:44.240 --> 04:45.410
Ow!

04:45.490 --> 04:47.200
Melvin,
you stepped on my heel!

04:47.280 --> 04:48.410
It's not my fault!

04:48.490 --> 04:50.580
Howard's steppin' on
both my heels!

04:50.660 --> 04:52.250
Ow!
Sorry!

04:52.330 --> 04:54.000
Ow!
Sorry!

04:54.080 --> 04:55.540
Do you know
where the entrance is?

04:55.620 --> 04:59.170
It's supposed to be here
somewhere in the old library.

05:01.590 --> 05:05.220
Obviously, it's one of those
book lever thingies.

05:05.300 --> 05:07.800
Aha!

05:07.890 --> 05:10.220
Wait for it...

05:10.310 --> 05:12.680
Okay, the lever must be
one of the other books.

05:12.770 --> 05:17.810
♪♪

05:17.900 --> 05:21.480
Uh, guys...
it's over here!

05:23.150 --> 05:24.900
Ah!

05:24.990 --> 05:30.070
♪♪

05:30.160 --> 05:32.950
[ Indistinct murmuring ]

05:33.040 --> 05:38.620
♪♪

05:38.710 --> 05:44.090
♪♪

05:44.170 --> 05:47.930
So I said, "Rutiger, dear boy,
only an amateur wears

05:48.010 --> 05:50.510
the same pair of poagies
for sculling an octuple

05:50.600 --> 05:53.470
and playing jai alai
at the racquet club."

05:53.560 --> 05:54.810
[ Chuckles, slurps ]

05:54.890 --> 05:57.640
This is the Moss
and Scones society?

05:57.730 --> 06:00.810
I don't see a single weird
ritual going on in there.

06:00.900 --> 06:02.440
I thought<i> I</i> was boring.

06:02.520 --> 06:04.980
This is like watching
quill ink dry.

06:05.070 --> 06:06.990
Theo, I think I speak
for all of us

06:07.070 --> 06:11.870
when I say it's time
we get this party started.

06:11.950 --> 06:13.120
Oh?

06:13.200 --> 06:14.870
♪♪

06:14.950 --> 06:18.870
Dang. That's the fanciest pegbox
I've ever seen!

06:18.960 --> 06:20.120
[ Grunts ]

06:20.210 --> 06:21.290
Ava!
Be careful!

06:21.380 --> 06:23.960
I just need to get
a better -- Oop!

06:24.050 --> 06:25.800
[ Plays sour note ]
Oh.

06:25.880 --> 06:28.630
-[ Gasps ]
-Oh, shoo--

06:28.720 --> 06:31.550
It's okay.
I can reach the book.

06:31.640 --> 06:34.220
[ Grunting ]

06:34.310 --> 06:36.970
Oh! [ Grunts ]

06:37.060 --> 06:38.520
[ Gasps ]

06:38.600 --> 06:41.400
Wh-Where did you guys come from?

06:41.480 --> 06:44.360
We can't just leave her
out there! What do we do?

06:44.440 --> 06:46.650
You have to follow
your heart, Mortimer.

06:46.730 --> 06:50.110
Oh...
[ Grunts ]

06:50.200 --> 06:52.120
Oh!

06:52.200 --> 06:54.120
[ Grunts ]

06:54.200 --> 06:56.700
-[ Grunts ]
-Whoa!

06:59.040 --> 07:00.750
I'm with them.

07:02.960 --> 07:07.210
Looks like we have some spies,
gentlemonsters.

07:07.300 --> 07:08.970
Go easy on us!

07:12.760 --> 07:16.390
Moss and Scones!
Moss and Scones!

07:16.470 --> 07:20.600
No one trespasses
on Moss and Scones!

07:20.690 --> 07:24.360
Now, we don't take too kindly
to interlopers,

07:24.440 --> 07:26.400
do we, monsters?

07:26.480 --> 07:27.690
No, sir.

07:27.780 --> 07:31.450
And what do we do
with interlopers?

07:31.530 --> 07:34.200
Initiate them.

07:34.280 --> 07:35.490
Wait, really?

07:35.580 --> 07:37.370
Do we get to be
in your club after all?

07:37.450 --> 07:41.000
No. We're just going
to initiate you.

07:41.080 --> 07:42.330
[ Chuckles ]

07:42.420 --> 07:43.500
Wait!

07:43.580 --> 07:45.210
Wait for what,
Mcleod?

07:45.290 --> 07:48.920
Theo, if I remember correctly,
our society's full chant is...

07:49.010 --> 07:52.220
"No one trespasses
on the Moss and Scones

07:52.300 --> 07:55.390
unless they have
a good reason."

07:55.470 --> 07:58.390
Shoot. You're right.
We totally forgot!

07:58.470 --> 08:01.730
Do you guys have
a good reason?

08:01.810 --> 08:04.600
We were trying to start
our own secret society

08:04.690 --> 08:07.900
and we needed to spy on you
to get some pointers?

08:07.980 --> 08:09.230
Oh! Well,

08:09.320 --> 08:11.570
the more secret societies,
the merrier!

08:11.650 --> 08:13.030
Why didn't you
just say so?

08:13.110 --> 08:16.570
Because you guys already
rejected me, so we have...

08:16.660 --> 08:18.620
kind of a weird...
thing?

08:18.700 --> 08:20.950
Ah.
Right.

08:21.040 --> 08:22.580
Can we go?

08:22.660 --> 08:25.210
♪♪

08:25.290 --> 08:27.880
Take some mossy scones
for the road.

08:27.960 --> 08:29.960
Oh, I almost forgot.

08:30.050 --> 08:32.670
Here.
It's our official guidebook.

08:32.760 --> 08:35.220
This bad boy has everything
you need to know to get past

08:35.300 --> 08:38.220
Stuart and form
a secret society at Harvard.

08:38.300 --> 08:40.970
This is...
surprisingly nice of you.

08:41.060 --> 08:43.810
Of course.

08:43.890 --> 08:45.440
Here we are, folks.

08:45.520 --> 08:50.270
Everything we need to make
our secret society official.

08:52.190 --> 08:54.570
"Fools"?
Excuse me?

08:54.650 --> 08:58.030
"A pox on the village
from whence you crawled"?

08:58.120 --> 09:00.790
"Raspberries"?
What?!

09:00.870 --> 09:03.080
These don't seem like ways
to start a club!

09:03.160 --> 09:04.620
We've been lampooned!

09:04.710 --> 09:07.290
More like
Moss and Scoundrels!

09:07.380 --> 09:09.340
I can't believe those guys!

09:09.420 --> 09:11.050
I'm so mad, I could...

09:11.130 --> 09:12.550
raise my voice!

09:12.630 --> 09:14.130
-Ohh.
-Hey!

09:14.220 --> 09:16.090
Quit hogging
the fainting couch!

09:16.180 --> 09:17.550
Good hustle, team!

09:17.640 --> 09:19.600
Really lovin'
the emotional range!

09:19.680 --> 09:20.970
[ Knock on door ]

09:21.060 --> 09:22.470
Stuart: I'm coming in!

09:22.560 --> 09:24.600
[ Gasps ] It's Stuart
with the clipboard!

09:24.680 --> 09:29.060
All right, amateur hour,
are we ready for --

09:29.150 --> 09:31.610
[ All chuckling nervously ]

09:31.690 --> 09:34.650
[ Sighs ] Are we ready
for this assessment?

09:34.740 --> 09:36.610
Stuart, we just need
a little more --

09:36.700 --> 09:39.570
Oscar, please.
I've got this.

09:40.780 --> 09:42.700
[ Clears throat,
inhales deeply ]

09:42.790 --> 09:44.120
Please make us official, Stuart!

09:44.200 --> 09:45.750
Please, please, please,
please, please!

09:45.830 --> 09:48.120
We beg of you!
[Sobbing] Please!

09:48.210 --> 09:49.960
Mm...no.

09:50.040 --> 09:51.250
Seriously?

09:51.340 --> 09:54.840
With great clipboard
comes great responsibility.

09:54.920 --> 09:58.380
♪♪

09:59.760 --> 10:01.180
I'm sorry, Mortimer.

10:01.260 --> 10:04.970
All the clubs Hedgehog and I
started are deeply unofficial.

10:06.350 --> 10:07.690
You know what?

10:07.770 --> 10:10.020
When my little friend
came from the future here

10:10.100 --> 10:11.690
and asked me what I wanted,

10:11.770 --> 10:14.860
I told him that I wanted to be
in an official secret society,

10:14.940 --> 10:16.610
that I wanted to belong.

10:16.690 --> 10:19.530
But now, I'm realizing that
while we were all trying so hard

10:19.610 --> 10:21.570
to make an official
secret society,

10:21.660 --> 10:24.950
nobody even noticed
that we'd all become friends.

10:25.040 --> 10:27.870
So, no secret society?

10:27.960 --> 10:30.170
Oh, no.
We absolutely must.

10:30.250 --> 10:32.880
We'll just be
deeply unofficial.

10:32.960 --> 10:36.510
The Unofficial
Tiny Outburst Society!

10:36.590 --> 10:39.300
Well, I guess this is
a good time to go home.

10:39.380 --> 10:41.340
We'll miss you,
little friend.

10:41.430 --> 10:42.970
-Mm.
-Mm.

10:43.050 --> 10:45.640
Mm!

10:45.720 --> 10:48.020
Aw.

10:48.100 --> 10:49.890
When will I see
you again?

10:49.980 --> 10:51.940
Ah-ah!
No spoilers.

10:52.940 --> 10:55.360
Okay, guys.
Here we go.

10:57.150 --> 10:58.490
[ Exhales deeply ]

10:58.570 --> 11:01.070
[ Inhales deeply ]

11:01.160 --> 11:02.490
[ Clears throat ]

11:02.570 --> 11:05.450
I don't actually know
how to get back.

11:06.040 --> 11:12.080
♪♪

11:12.170 --> 11:18.260
♪♪

11:18.340 --> 11:20.670
-Ow!
-Sorry.
